//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_director_divest}

NOTE: This operation divests a {rbtr_director} {giam_service_account} from the {rbtgi_depot_project}.
The {rbtr_governor} reads the role's installed RBRA, extracts the SA email from the `client_email` field, issues a REST DELETE against the IAM API, and removes the production RBRA file from disk to mirror cloud state and prevent stale-credential reuse.
No arguments required; the target SA is derived entirely from the kindled regime and the role's installed credential file.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_governor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Read Role RBRA and Extract Service Account Email*:
.. {rbbc_require}
the role's installed RBRA file exists at
{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if the file is missing: "Director RBRA file not found — director may not have been invested"
.. {rbbc_store}
`«SA_EMAIL»` from the `client_email` field of
{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `client_email` is empty or absent: "Director RBRA file present but client_email field is missing or empty"

//axhos_step
. *Divest Director Service Account*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/delete[iam.projects.serviceAccounts.delete] with:
... method: `DELETE`
... endpoint: `https://iam.googleapis.com/v1/projects/{rbtgi_depot_project}/serviceAccounts/«SA_EMAIL»`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «GOVERNOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response OR HTTP 404 (already divested)
.. {rbbc_warn}
if HTTP 404: "Service account not found (already divested)"

//axhos_step
. *Remove Production RBRA File*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_rbra_remove}
for the role's RBRA file at
{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if the file cannot be removed: "Failed to remove director RBRA file — manual cleanup required"
.. NOTE: Removing the RBRA file mirrors cloud state locally and prevents any process from reusing a credential that no longer corresponds to an active
{giam_service_account}.

//axhos_step
. *Display Result*:
.. {rbbc_show}
single-line success naming `«SA_EMAIL»` and confirming the
{rbtr_director}
{giam_service_account}
was divested, or a notice that it was already absent

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution removes the
{rbtr_director}
{giam_service_account}
from
{rbtgi_depot_project}
and deletes the local RBRA credential file.
Cloud state and local credential state are left in agreement: no stale key file remains after a successful divest.
A 404 response from the cloud DELETE is accepted as success — the
{giam_service_account}
is absent either way, and the RBRA file is removed regardless.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_retriever_divest}

NOTE: This operation divests a {rbtr_retriever} {giam_service_account} from the {rbtgi_depot_project}.
The {rbtr_governor} reads the retriever's installed RBRA, extracts the SA email from the RBRA's `client_email` field, issues a REST DELETE against the IAM API, and removes the production RBRA file from disk to mirror cloud state and prevent stale-credential reuse.
No arguments are required; the target SA is derived entirely from the kindled regime and the retriever's installed credential file.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as {rbtr_governor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Read Retriever RBRA and Extract SA Email*:
.. {rbbc_require}
RBRA file present at
{rbrr_retriever_rbra_file}
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if file missing: "Retriever RBRA file not found — retriever may not be invested"
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»` from RBRA's `client_email` field
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»` is empty or absent: "client_email field missing from retriever RBRA"

//axhos_step
. *Divest Retriever Service Account*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/delete[iam.projects.serviceAccounts.delete] with:
... method: `DELETE`
... endpoint: `https://iam.googleapis.com/v1/projects/{rbtgi_depot_project}/serviceAccounts/«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «GOVERNOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response OR HTTP 404 (already divested)
.. {rbbc_warn}
if HTTP 404: "Retriever service account not found in cloud (already divested)"

//axhos_step
. *Remove Production RBRA File*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_rbra_remove}
for the retriever's RBRA file at
{rbrr_retriever_rbra_file},
mirroring cloud state and preventing stale-credential reuse
.. {rbbc_require}
file removal successful or file already absent

//axhos_step
. *Display Result*:
.. {rbbc_show}
single-line success notice naming `«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»` and confirming divestiture, or a 404-already-gone notice if cloud state was already clean

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution removes the {rbtr_retriever} {giam_service_account} from the {rbtgi_depot_project} and deletes the production RBRA file, leaving no stale credentials on disk.
Proceed to
{rbtgo_retriever_invest}
to re-issue a fresh retriever SA when needed.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_director_roster}

NOTE: This operation rosters {rbtr_director} {giam_service_account_s} in the {rbtgi_depot_project} via per-SA fact-file emission.
Read-only observation: lists all SAs, filters to director-prefixed accountIds, and emits one fact per discovered SA via {buf_write_fact_multi} against the `RBCC_fact_ext_roster_director` extension constant.
Fact content is empty (presence-as-fact); stdout assertion of individual identities is retired.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_governor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` from the resulting access token

//axhos_step
. *List service accounts*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/list[iam.projects.serviceAccounts.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `https://iam.googleapis.com/v1/projects/{rbtgi_depot_project}/serviceAccounts`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «GOVERNOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ACCOUNTS»` from response `.accounts[]` array

//axhos_step
. *Filter to director service accounts*:
.. From `«ACCOUNTS»`, retain only entries whose `.accountId` begins with the `${RBCC_role_director}-` prefix
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_ACCOUNTS»` — the filtered set; per-role observation per BBAAQ contract

//axhos_step
. *Emit Fact Per Discovered {rbtr_director}*:
.. For each entry in `«DIRECTOR_ACCOUNTS»`:
... {rbbc_store}
`«IDENTITY»` by stripping the `${RBCC_role_director}-` prefix from the entry's `accountId`
... {rbbc_call}
{buf_write_fact_multi}
with three positional arguments:
.... `<file_root>`: composed as `<roster_subdir>/«IDENTITY»` (the basename root for the emitted fact file)
.... `<ext>`: `RBCC_fact_ext_roster_director` (resolves at source time to `roster-director`)
.... `<value>`: `""` (empty content — presence-as-fact convention per RBS0:1081)

//axhos_step
. *Report count*:
.. {rbbc_show}
total count of emitted director fact files

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution rosters {rbtr_director} service accounts via per-SA fact emission — one `roster-director` fact file per discovered identity.
The operation is read-only; no service accounts are created or modified.

